"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-lifestyle-celeb-news-local-celebs-tatjana-smith-medals-olympics-husband-parents-nationality-christian-faith\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bb'No medal can compare': Tatjana on treasuring her Christian faith  Swimming sensation Tatjana Smith has proudly revealed that her Olympic gold medals are insignificant to her Christian faith\\u2026  Tatjana Smith has proudly revealed that winning a gold medal at the Olympics has no comparison to her strong faith in God. The Christian swimmer recently won first and second place in the 100m and 200 breaststroke, respectively.  The 27-year-old has now retired and is planning to pursue the next chapter of her life.  On her Instagram Stories, Tatjana Smith shared a quote she had said after winning gold and silver in the Olympics.  She said, \\\"No medal will ever compare to the feeling you have when you 100% trust in God for the outcome, win or lose. This time, I am humbled to have won.\\\"  The post shared on the Instagram account @_christhlete, was liked by Springboks captain Siya Kolisi, whose wife Rachel is the sister of Tatjana's husband, Joel Smith.  Siya commented: \\\"Amen and amen.\\\"  A post shared by Christian Athletes(Chris\\u271ehlete\\u2122\\ufe0f) (@_christhlete)  Last week, the 27-year-oldwore a T-shirt with the namesof all those who had helped her succeed in her swimming career. At the top of the list was \\\"God, Jesus, and Holy Spirit\\\".  Tatjana also revealed that shefavoured wearing her cross earringswhile competing in races.  She said: \\\"It just represents something about me and why I do it. It's to glorify God and does not necessarily mean winning gold medals.\\\"  Like Tatjana Smith, Olympic sprinter Wayde van Niekerk has also spoken fervently about his faith.  At the 2016 Olympics in Rio, Wayde said of his record-breaking gold win in the 400m: \\\"Jesus did it\\\".  A picture of the star's running shoes with the handwritten words: \\\"Jesus, I am all yours. Use me\\\" went viral around the world.  Speaking to the media after his victory, the emotional athlete said: \\\"Everything that comes my way, I thank the Lord. I leave every race and every step I take in his hands. I trust him in every movement I do.\\\"  After missing out on the 2021 Tokyo Olympics due to an injury, Wayde van Niekerk will run in the 2024 Paris Olympics in the 200m heats on Monday, 5 August.  'The South African' is hiring! Freelance writer positions available. Send us your CV  The draw for Rugby World Cup 2027 will take place in Sydney, Australia on Wednesday, 3 December at 11:00 (SA time).  Today's Daily Lotto jackpot stands at an estimated R550 000. If you want to win your share of the jackpot, you have to play!  Faberge's The Winter Egg, fetched a record \\u00a322.9 million (R518 million) at auction on Tuesday, Christie's said.  Former Pirates star Phumudzo Manenzhe has discussed the exclusion of Thapelo Morena from Bafana Bafana's AFCON 2025 squad.  Kaizer Chiefs will play their penultimate match of 2025 on Wednesday, 3 December when they visit Chippa United in Gqeberha.  Secures a NEW shopping bag? Woolworths has seemingly disassociated itself with the testimony of 'tenderpreneur' Vusi 'Cat Matlala\\u2026    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"